               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Rawḍat al-aḥbāb fī siyar al-Nabī wa-al-āl wa-al-aṣḥāb by Dashtakī, ʻAṭāʼ Allāh ibn Faḍl Allāh, -1400 or 1401&gt;
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="CODRINGTON.READE_NO_18_BOX_8-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/16882481" key="person_16882481">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Dashtakī, ʻAṭāʼ Allāh ibn Faḍl Allāh, -1400 or 1401&gt;</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دشتکی، عطا الله بن فضل</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1946">Rawḍat al-aḥbāb fī siyar al-Nabī wa-al-āl wa-al-aṣḥāb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1946">روضة الاحباب في سير النبي والآل والاصحاب</title>
                     <note>Inside front cover: In pencil: Morley's catalogue numbers. Flyleaf, recto: In ink: 72; title in English and Arabic; 'Presented by Sir J Malcolm May 19 1827; In pencil: title and description. Flyleaf, verso: no: 15 I.? L Folio 1, recto: a) Note of purchase for? the library of Muhammad Hafeez b, Shaikh Hamid 'Uthmani for 130 rupees on 1 Sha'ban, year one of Rafi' al-Darajat. Written at the request of the Timurid minister Mir 'Ali Shir Nawa'i.With curse on anyone claiming ownership. Accompanied by small oval seal, presumably of the said Hafeez: Ya Hafiz Ya Hafeez 1126, regnal year probably 3. b) Partly effaced note of purchase dated 21 Ramazan (mis-spelt), regnal year one. c) Effaced note with seal. A History of the life and actions of Muhammad, his companions and their disciples. This manuscript contains only the first of the three maqsads or divisions of the book. End of scribe's name in damaged colophon: ... Muhammad walad Isma'il Musawi. Illuminated initial opening. Ruled margins. Rubricated headings and punctuation. Occasional marginal notes.</note>
                     <incipit>Al-hamdu lillah alladhi manna 'ala al-mu'minin idh ba'atha fihum rasulan minhum</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 189-92.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, pp. 146-7.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, Nos 145, 146-57.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For Malcolm's gift see the Donations Register for 19 May 1827 and the Transactions for 1830, pp. xcix-c.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
